Details: Comparison between DI-DQ_Complete_SP (complete Snowflake stored procedure) and DI-DQ_Incomplete_Response (request for missing files). Significant divergence in approach and completeness, with one agent providing a full solution and the other requesting additional information.

DI-DQ_Complete_SP provides comprehensive DQ validation logic with 15 specific rules covering nullability, format validation, uniqueness, and referential integrity. DI-DQ_Incomplete_Response acknowledges the task but requests missing DDL files instead of attempting implementation. Fundamental difference in problem-solving approach.

DI-DQ_Complete_SP follows standard stored procedure structure with sequence creation (lines 7-8), procedure definition (lines 10-11), JavaScript implementation (lines 13-65), and systematic rule processing (lines 35-60). DI-DQ_Incomplete_Response has no comparable structure - single paragraph text format with no code organization.

Minor syntax issues: Line 31 regex pattern missing proper escaping for backslashes, Line 33 REGEXP_MATCHES should be REGEXP, Line 37 similar regex escaping issue. JavaScript connection handling lacks proper error handling in lines 18-22.
Grammatically correct and properly formatted message. No syntax errors in the text content.
Average correctness score across both agents.

Fix regex patterns by properly escaping backslashes, replace REGEXP_MATCHES with REGEXP function, add comprehensive error handling for database connections, and validate connection parameters before execution.
